        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         In the good old days, circa a week ago, when Robinhood was still Robin Hood and st0nks only went up, there was a meme that circulated every so often about what would happen to the market when Robinhood went public and Robinhood traders could trade Robinhood shares on Robinhood. Woah.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         It reminded me of that scene in
         <em>
          <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkD1vhDAMhn8NGVE-yJEOGSpVp_a2bt1QIAaigyQKzlH-fXPHUMuyJVv2q_cZDMIU0qFj2JA8S4dHBO1h3xZAhETyBqlzVrMLV0I2b8TqxjIlFXFbNyaA1bhFY8pAYu4XNxh0wb8uKOWSzLoFZWxr-8soWmVF-2bshY1jQ0FaJYfx1DXZOvADaHhAOoIHsugZMW6VeK_4teS-7_URMuYe6iGsz4nBYa7E9VGJj-UrwkPdfm6f38RpTjmjnDImZIma1WsffyOkJoqhaug68XrL_YZmuD9_kaR9wD4k56eyvs9mheW1KJ660tfsHR4deNMvYE-7eFJ7Aegm8JAKTdsZLKwYZ6ptpeRSnvYKD8GpEi1tSFG2oVz5f9E_dHSF7A" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
           Being John Malkovich
          </a>
         </em>
         , the one in which John Malkovich goes through his own portal and ends up surrounded by other John Malkoviches who can only say, \xe2\x80\x9cMalkovich.\xe2\x80\x9d
        </p>
