        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         In May 2018, it raised a
         <strong>
          <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2OhCAQhU_T7DSA0o0LFrOZaxh-SiUqECi7x9sPo4upkCKVyst79VmNMMd8qhQLkr824plABfiUDRAhk6NAHr1T7MllJ_qBONU7JoUkvoxTBti13xTmA0g6zOatRh_DpaCUC7IoKZzrhaW074ZJDnIyXA_C0Kd2nGuA21cfzkOwoOAN-YwByKYWxFQe3deDf9eXPNrFxLi2Nu51_g9ZhxyND0uMrjRvvR1XiKasZ452BSzNx-PSbPXcgs3kgw7Wh5l4xSlnlFPGOlGrZe1u0k-C3KfOPnq6z7wthymo7WVLsgoRTcxVXdfronfYrkU9fqz_fgSP5whBmw3czQVvvBepcYYAueZwo8YKlXEmXy8huBA3hwqu41R2L9qT6uxiVYV_01-hhZcy" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
           $363 million Series D
          </a>
         </strong>
         at a $5.6 billion valuation. More than 3x growth in valuation in eight months implies that options trading was working well for the company, but it also introduced a whole new level of risk, for users and for the company itself.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Between the Series C in 2017 and the beginning of 2020, Robinhood grew steadily from 2 million to 10 million users. Then COVID hit, and things started to get really interesting. Robinhood added 3 million users in the first three months of the pandemic. By October,
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxVkduKwyAQhp8m3rVEjUl64cXC0tcIRqepNB7QsYd9-rVJYVnxAP8_wy_faIWwhPSSMWQk72vCVwTp4ZFXQIRESoY0WSNpz0YuuhMxsjN0FCOxebokAKfsKjEVILHMq9UKbfBbR9syQa6SKjGMivfiMp46NpyAidnABXrTdzD2dM9VxVjwGiTcIb2CB7LKK2LMDf9q2LludUvK5aR-QjrmMmdU-nbUwVUr1oNXOOhwt-bgVLoBNvycGv69xmet6Au6SSsXlV18Vd-RH9WBscVV7QHzR8qhJA1VwofdIFjJWkZb1lLKRV1HenRzfEZIXeS66Vq3sH9_Ikn6gHNI1i_Vvl2Vg3UzKqSpvq54i68JvJpXMDs_3MewEZ0W8JDqeMyksMKnjI7DIAQTYudVAXPWjnxoO1KTTahd_i_0F06novU" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          akram\xe2\x80\x99s razor estimated
         </a>
         it had 16 million users.
        </p>
